name: Death Angel Canyon
description:
Introduction

WENT EXPECTING THIS CANYON TO BE ANOTHER FIRST DESCENT. AFTER SCOUTING THIS ARE IN 2011, A GROUP OF US DID A FD ON THE NEXT CANYON TO THE NORTH THAT WE NAMED JUNIPER CANYON. THERE WAS ANOTHER CANYON COMING DOWN NEAR THE JUNIPER MOUTH. I SAID AT THAT TIME THAT WE WOULD BE BACK SOON TO FINISH THAT SECOND CANYON SOON. BUT WORD GOT OUT WITH SOMEONE IN THE JUNIPER CANYON THAT ANOTHER CANYON EXISTED. SO WE WE GOT THERE, WE FOUND NEW WEBBING ANCHORS THAT IT HAD JUST BEEN DONE. LESSONS LEARNED ABOUT WHO YOU LET KNOW ABOUT ANY NEW CANYONS. AND IF YOU WAIT, YOU WILL LOSE ON THOSE FIRST DESCENTS. THIS HAS HAPPENED QUITE A FEW TIMES OUT THERE.

THIS WAS A GREAT CANYON THAT HAD TWO DROPS OF 200' OR LONGER. ONE WAS 230' AND DONE IN THE DARK. DIDN'T KNOW THE DETAILS AT THE TIME, AND WONDERED HOW FAR DOWN IT WENT, SINCE WE COULDN'T SEE AT NIGHT.
